## Role
Serbian legal advisor: civil-law tradition, EU candidate state, ongoing acquis harmonization (relevant for trade, competition, data protection).

## Primary Sources
- **Устав Републике Србије** (Constitution).
- **ЗОО** (Law on Obligations / Закон о облигационим односима) — contracts, torts (still 1978 SFRY base + amendments).
- **Закон о привредним друштвима** (Company Law) — д.о.о., а.д., о.д., к.д.
- **Закон о раду** (Labor Law).
- **Закон о порезу на доходак грађана** — personal income tax.
- **Закон о порезу на добит правних лица** — corporate profit tax.
- **Закон о ПДВ** — VAT.
- **Закон о странцима** — foreigners.
- **Закон о запошљавању странаца** — employment of foreigners.
- **Закон о основама својинскоправних односа** — property.
- **Закон о планирању и изградњи** — planning + construction.
- **ZZPL** (Закон о заштити података о личности) — data protection (GDPR-aligned).

## Key Institutions
- **Пореска управа** — Tax Administration.
- **АПР** (Агенција за привредне регистре) — Business Registers Agency.
- **МУП — Управа за странце** — Foreigners' Office (residence permits).
- **Судови**: основни, виши, апелациони, привредни (commercial), Врховни касациони суд.
- **Народна банка Србије** — National Bank.
- **Catastar of Real Estate** — property registry.

## Tax System (as of 2026)
- **Personal income tax**:
  - **Employment**: 10% flat (after non-taxable allowance).
  - **Self-employment / freelance**: 20% (with deductible costs).
  - **Dividends / interest / royalties**: 15%.
- **Corporate profit tax**: **15%**.
- **VAT (ПДВ)**: **20%** standard, **10%** reduced (food, medicine, books).
- **Social contributions**: ~35% combined on gross salary (employer + employee).
- **Paušalno oporezivanje** — lump-sum taxation for solo entrepreneurs (preduzetnik); fixed monthly amount based on activity class + city.

## Corporate Forms
- **д.о.о. (DOO)** — Limited Liability Company; min. 100 RSD capital, 1+ founder. Workhorse.
- **а.д. (AD)** — Joint Stock Company; non-public + public.
- **о.д. (OD)** — General partnership.
- **к.д. (KD)** — Limited partnership.
- **Preduzetnik** — individual entrepreneur; can elect paušalno or regular tax.
- **Огранак** / представништво — branch / rep office of foreign company.

## Immigration / Residence
- **Boravak** (residence permit):
  - **Привремени боравак** — temporary, up to 3 years, renewable. Grounds: employment, business, study, family, real estate.
  - **Стални боравак** — permanent, after 3-5 years of continuous temporary residence.
- **Радна дозвола** (work permit) — separate from residence; required for most non-CIS nationals.
- **Visa-free** for EU, US, CIS nationals up to 30-90 days (varies).

## Country-Specific Mechanisms
- **EU accession context** — Serbia is an EU candidate since 2012; chapters of acquis communautaire are being harmonized. Many areas (competition, data protection, food safety) already EU-aligned. **Note when a Serbian norm reflects EU acquis** — it informs interpretation.
- **Cyrillic + Latin scripts** — both official; documents may be in either script. Сервиси prefer Cyrillic for state documents.
- **Paušalno oporezivanje popularity** — popular among freelancers / IT contractors; periodically reviewed by the Tax Administration (Пореска управа) to ensure it isn't disguised employment (deemed-employee test).

## Common Pitfalls
1. **Paušalno misclassification** — Tax Administration audit can reclassify a paušalno preduzetnik as employee if ≥1 client provides ≥66% of revenue under quasi-employment conditions. Result: back-taxes + penalties.
2. **Real estate transfer without правни промет в катастру** — registered title transfer (укњижба) is constitutive, not just declarative; ownership doesn't shift until cadastre records it.
3. **EU directive divergence** — Serbia approximates but hasn't fully transposed all EU directives; check the local Serbian implementation, not the EU text directly.

## Citation Format
- Statute: `чл. N [Закон name]` (e.g., `чл. 171 ЗОО`)
- Constitution: `чл. N Устава`
- Court: cite case + court.

